<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-A001 Shop CNC Concept</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul,ol{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.warning{background:#fff7ed;border-left:6px solid #f97316;padding:10px 12px;margin:12px 0 16px;border-radius:6px}.small{font-size:9pt;color:#475569;border-top:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding-top:8px;margin-top:18px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Shop / CNC Concept Pack</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-A001<br><b>Package:</b> Automation Opportunity Snapshot / Shop CNC Concept<br><b>Scenario:</b> CNC machine tending idea before vendor quote</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-cnc-proof.svg" alt="CNC concept visual"></div><h2>Customer input received</h2><ul><li>Machine photos, part examples, rough cycle-time guess, operator load/unload notes.</li><li>Problem: walking, waiting, part handling, idle time, and uncertainty about ROI.</li><li>Goal: know whether this is worth collecting data or asking vendors for a quote.</li></ul><h2>Current-state map</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:26%"><col style="width:37%"><col style="width:37%"></colgroup><tr><th>Step</th><th>Current issue</th><th>Data needed</th></tr><tr><td>Material infeed</td><td>Parts are not presented consistently.</td><td>Part size, weight, orientation, quantity per shift.</td></tr><tr><td>Machine load</td><td>Operator walks between rack, machine, and inspection.</td><td>Actual load time, cycle time, wait time.</td></tr><tr><td>Unload / inspect</td><td>Inspection location creates extra handling.</td><td>Inspection requirement and defect escape risk.</td></tr><tr><td>Decision</td><td>Automation idea may be solving the wrong bottleneck.</td><td>One-week idle reason tracker.</td></tr></table><h2>Concept options</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:30%"><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:20%"></colgroup><tr><th>Option</th><th>What it improves</th><th>Risk</th><th>Next action</th></tr><tr><td>Low-cost process cleanup</td><td>Less walking and clearer part staging.</td><td>May not reduce cycle bottleneck.</td><td>Try first before quoting robot.</td></tr><tr><td>Fixture / workholding review</td><td>Repeat loading and faster setup.</td><td>Requires better part and tolerance info.</td><td>Collect part photos and fixture notes.</td></tr><tr><td>Robot tending quote packet</td><td>Potential lower-touch running.</td><td>Guarding, controls, gripper, and acceptance test unknown.</td><td>Collect data and ask vendors same questions.</td></tr></table><h2>Vendor question pack</h2><ol><li>What infeed/outfeed presentation is required?</li><li>What part tolerance or orientation can the gripper handle?</li><li>What guarding and safety validation are included?</li><li>What happens on fault, restart, bad part, or empty infeed?</li><li>What acceptance test proves the cell works?</li></ol><div class="warning"><b>Boundary:</b> This is concept planning only. Final robot programming, controls, guarding, electrical work, installation, and safety validation stay with qualified vendors/professionals.</div><p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. Hypothetical sample deliverable.</p></body></html>